    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Yes it's the expected behaviour the call to the method `setQueryParameter` ([actually every changes to the search parameters](https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-helper-js#automatic-reset-to-page-0)) reset the page automatically. You have to save the page before calling the method then re-apply it after.\r\n\r\n```js\r\n{\r\n  searchFunction: function(helper) {\r\n    var query = helper.state.query;\r\n    var page = helper.state.page;\r\n\r\n    if (query === \"\") {\r\n      helper.setQueryParameter(\"aroundPrecision\", 50 * metersInMile);\r\n    } else {\r\n      helper.setQueryParameter(\"aroundPrecision\", 500 * metersInMile);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    helper.setPage(page).search();\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n```",
